Gears align. I'm Mina. I play the organ for
the chapel. Welcome to the city.
You produce the letter addressed to Mina, and hand it
over to her. She looks at you tentatively, not yet opening
We found it on the celestial path. We took it
from the body of a dead man. It was quite deep
in the woods, i'm not sure if he was lost or
She opens the seal, and carefully slides out the letter.
Her hand unwittingly covers her mouth as she reads it,
before looking back up at you, wide eyed.
This letter...it's from my playing partner,
Vlad. Between us, we play music for the chapel.
What was he doing all the way out at the
celestial path? It's quite far from here, not
It says that he was looking to cross the
Aetherflow, and get to Castle Altair...that
he'd learned of a conspiracy amongst the
I'm Elim, the captain of the Altair Kingsguard
but we hadn't heard anything from Vlad at all.
Why did he have a letter addressed to you on
From what I read, it seems to be some sort of
failsafe, in case he didn't make it. He hoped
this letter would find its way back to me, and
then he wanted me to warn Castle Altair.
Consider us warned then. Did he say anything
more about what the conspiracy was?
Its very vague, I assume to keep the news
secret if this letter was intercepted. But it
seems to allude to someone in the council not
acting in the best interests of the city.
I take it, that it doesn't say who?

here, and for telling me about Vlad. I will
